    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "A deliberate color. Chateau Green works on craftsman, traditional, and cottage-style elevations where the roof is meant to grow out of the landscape. The granule blend uses dark olive and brown accents to keep the surface visually warm.",
      "The shingle profile carries a deep shadow line that emphasizes the green tone in late-morning light. Mid-day the surface looks almost dark gray; at golden hour the green pulls forward.",
      "Works best on craftsman, traditional, and rustic-cottage builds. Stays clear of contemporary all-white elevations where the green can read as period-incorrect."
